net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.composite

Class CustomCellRenderer

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Label
        • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.composite.CustomCellRenderer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Component>, net.proteusframework.core.locale.LocaleContextSource, Component, ListCellRenderer, TableCellRenderer, TreeCellRenderer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CustomValueRenderer

    public class CustomCellRenderer
extends Label
    Customizable cell renderer. By default this implementation handles rendering of OptionallyLocalizedNamedObject, LocalizedNamedObject, Date, NULL values, and Collections.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@proteus.co)

      • getCellValueAsText

        protected @NonNull net.proteusframework.core.locale.TextSource getCellValueAsText(java.lang.Object value)
        Description copied from class: Label
        Get the String representation of a cell value. Override this method to customize how a cell value is displayed. This method is called from all cell renderer methods. It is called from the Label.validate() method so the component is attached.
        Support exists for the following value types.
        • NULL
        • *NamedObject
        • Date
        • Collection
        • Arrays
        Overrides:
        getCellValueAsText in class Label
        Parameters:
        value - the cell value.
        Returns:
        text.
